# Estimands in benchmarking

- **High-level goal:** 
  - "Equal protection" of law for "similarly situated" individuals,
    <br>$\mathbb{E}[S(r_0) | X=x, D=d] = \mathbb{E}[S(r_1) | X=x, D=d]$
- Common considerations:
  - Estimand should remain interpretable when outcome is rare
  - Focus on violator subgroup with $D=d_1$ to avoid dilution
  - If in litigation, showing harm specifically to $R=r_1$ subgroup

<table style="font-size: 30px; margin-left: 1em; margin-top: -1ex">
<col style="width: 12em">
<col style="width: 10em">
<tr>
<td>
$$
\frac{
{\color{white}\sum_x \ } \mathbb{E}[S(r_1) | x, d_1] \ {\color{white} w_x}
}{
{\color{white}\sum_x \ } \mathbb{E}[S(r_0) | x, d_1] \ {\color{white} w_x}
}{\color{white},}
$$
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: middle">
$$
\color{white} w_x = p(x | d_1)
$$
</td>
</tr>
</table>


.footnote[
<table style="left: 5%; width: 95%; font-size: 20px">
<col style="width: 5%">
<col style="width: 90%">
  <tr>
    <td align="center"><strong style="">[1]</strong></td>
    <td>Knox & Mummolo. 2025. "New data fill longstanding gaps in the study of policing." <i>Science</i>.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
]

---

# Estimands in benchmarking

- **High-level goal:** 
  - "Equal protection" of law for "similarly situated" individuals,
    <br>$\mathbb{E}[S(r_0) | X=x, D=d] = \mathbb{E}[S(r_1) | X=x, D=d]$
- Common considerations:
  - Estimand should remain interpretable when outcome is rare
  - Focus on violator subgroup with $D=d_1$ to avoid dilution
  - If in litigation, showing harm specifically to $R=r_1$ subgroup

<table style="font-size: 30px; margin-left: 1em; margin-top: -1ex">
<col style="width: 12em">
<col style="width: 10em">
<tr>
<td>
$$
\frac{
\sum_x \ \mathbb{E}[S(r_1) | x, d_1] \ w_x
}{
\sum_x \ \mathbb{E}[S(r_0) | x, d_1] \ w_x
},
$$
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: middle">
$$
\color{#A51C30} w_x = \Pr(x | d_1)
$$
</td>
</tr>
</table>


.footnote[
<table style="left: 5%; width: 95%; font-size: 20px">
<col style="width: 5%">
<col style="width: 90%">
  <tr>
    <td align="center"><strong style="">[1]</strong></td>
    <td>Knox & Mummolo. 2025. "New data fill longstanding gaps in the study of policing." <i>Science</i>.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
]

---

# Estimands in benchmarking

- **High-level goal:** 
  - "Equal protection" of law for "similarly situated" individuals,
    <br>$\mathbb{E}[S(r_0) | X=x, D=d] = \mathbb{E}[S(r_1) | X=x, D=d]$
- Common considerations:
  - Estimand should remain interpretable when outcome is rare
  - Focus on violator subgroup with $D=d_1$ to avoid dilution
  - If in litigation, showing harm specifically to $R=r_1$ subgroup

<table style="font-size: 30px; margin-left: 1em; margin-top: -1ex">
<col style="width: 12em">
<col style="width: 10em">
<tr>
<td>
$$
\frac{
\sum_x \ \mathbb{E}[S(r_1) | x, d_1] \ w_x
}{
\sum_x \ \mathbb{E}[S(r_0) | x, d_1] \ w_x
},
$$
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: middle">
$$
\color{#A51C30} w_x = \Pr(x | d_1, r_1)
$$
</td>
</tr>
</table>


.footnote[
<table style="left: 5%; width: 95%; font-size: 20px">
<col style="width: 5%">
<col style="width: 90%">
  <tr>
    <td align="center"><strong style="">[1]</strong></td>
    <td>Knox & Mummolo. 2025. "New data fill longstanding gaps in the study of policing." <i>Science</i>.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
]

